The hardware consists of a linux machine connected with a wireless interface with monitor mode capabilities.

You the program do following functions:
- enable/disable monitor mode for the wireless interface
- turn on/off the wireless interface - while

in monitor mode and on:

a. list all the wifi clients that are currently in range of the wireless interface
(this list refresh automatically and clients which dropped out of range removed from the list).
Also give details related with signal strength and time spent in range

b. log of all the wifi clients (those currently in range as well as all historical)
together with time spent in range and number of times client came in range.

c. Selecting any wifi client bring up a histogram of signal strength recorded, details of times spent in range.

